        <heading>3326.  Effect of mortgage filed after death of mortgagor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3326.  Effect of mortgage filed after death of mortgagor
A judgment or a conventional mortgage filed for recordation more than twenty days after the mortgagor dies gives no preference to the mortgagee over the other creditors of the estate of the deceased if the estate is insufficient to satisfy all the creditors.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110376</p>
        </authorialNote>
